 as 
\begin_inset Formula $\underset{q\rightarrow0}{lim}\left(\dfrac{\mathbf{F}}{q}\right)$
\end_inset

 where q is the test charge and F is the force acting on it.
 What is the physical significance of 
\begin_inset Formula $\underset{q\rightarrow0}{lim}$
\end_inset

 in this expression ? Draw the electric field lines of a point charge Q
 when (i) Q > 0 and (ii) Q < 0.
\end_layout

